latestIgtvVideos.title: Social Media Addiction - Short Film
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
In today's time, social media is helpful but its addiction can be harmful and that is what has been shown in this film. 

Social media addiction is a story of a young girl who spends most of a day on the phone, whether it's talking to her friends or posting something online. She tries her best to portray her life as happening as she can when the truth is, that it is just like any other teenager. Showing this unreal side of her life on social media made her happy until she gets into trouble. 

This five minute film captures the impact of social media on the life of teenagers, but the message and outcome is relevant for all social media addicts.

Actor- @yuktachanda 
Shot and edited by - @thebeautifulimperfection

latestIgtvVideos.title: You cannot expect someone else to keep you happy.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This is my quarantine story in which I realised that I AM INCHARGE OF MY OWN LIFE and then I took control of it. 
It is so important to understand that you need to give your time and your hundred percent efforts to yourself first before giving it to someone else. 
Disclaimer- In no way I am implying that you need to spend your quarantine productivity, instead you can relax and do whatever suits you and your mental health.

When traveling to London, there are several things that often go unmentioned but can significantly enhance your experience. Here are some of them:

1. Transport Tips: The London Underground (Tube) can be confusing for first-time travelers. Familiarize yourself with the map and consider downloading a transport app for real-time updates. Avoid peak hours if possible, as trains can be packed.

2. Walking is Key: Many of London’s attractions are within walking distance of each other. Don’t underestimate the charm of exploring on foot, as you’ll discover hidden gems along the way.

3. Free Attractions: London has numerous free attractions, including museums like the British Museum and the National Gallery. Take advantage of these to save money while exploring.

4. Weather Variability: London weather can change rapidly. It’s wise to carry an umbrella and dress in layers, as you might encounter sunshine, rain, and wind all in one day.

5. Dining Etiquette: Tipping is customary in restaurants, generally around 10-15%. However, check your bill first, as some places include a service charge.

6. Local Customs: Be aware of local customs, such as queuing politely and saying “please” and “thank you.” Londoners appreciate good manners.

7. Safety: While London is relatively safe, be mindful of your belongings, especially in crowded areas. Pickpocketing can occur in tourist hotspots.

8. Cash vs. Card: Although many places accept credit and debit cards, it’s useful to have some cash on hand for small purchases, especially in markets or smaller shops.

9. Cultural Events: London often hosts free festivals, street performances, and pop-up markets. Check local event listings to find something exciting happening during your visit.
